{
  "stem": "7458.4",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "He had-- he had just married a lovely blonde young woman, Sally, who is still his wife in Montreal, and who makes the best kreplach in the whole world.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "But in any event, so he insisted that I spend a day or two with them.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And he said he would drive me and I would catch up with the train, because the trains would go a little ways and stop and go a little ways, and I would catch up with my train and continue leading.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "So I spent a day or two with him.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And when we caught up with the train a couple days later, we found that the train was in a collision.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And a couple of the people from my hometown that were part of the group I was leading were killed.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "In fact, I have a picture of one of them in the album there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "Two of his sons survived and are in Israel now, Poplovsky, David and [INAUDIBLE] Poplovksy.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "But the father was killed in the train wreck.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And had I been on that train, I might have been killed as well.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "But because I met up with Sholom and he took me off the train, I avoided that collision.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "Eventually, I ended up being shot.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "We were crossing a border illegally at night and some soldiers fired.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "And the bullet hit me right here through my hand and my groin.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "And I ended up in a hospital in Italy.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "And I have pictures of that also.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "And while in the hospital in Italy, I found out that I had an aunt in Rochester, New York, Mary Kaufman, my mother's sister, who found out about me through an organization that was helping people locate relatives.",
      "word_count": 38
    }
  ],
